==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immolation
<hw>Im`mo*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immolatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>immolation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of immolating, or the state of being immolated, or
sacrificed.</def> <rj><au>Sir. T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is immolated; a sacrifice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Destruction by fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immolator</ent>⟦br⟧
